# Clothoid chord-length residual monotonicity, Qed-closed conditional theorem
# (Stdlib lane).  Realises the "next concrete Azimuth.v target" named in
# Azimuth.v's cross-corpus bridge block: |kappa*L| <= pi connected to
# f'(L) > 0.  The derivative identities enter as Section hypotheses (H_deriv,
# H_fprime_pos), witnessed Qed in the proprietary companion
# clothoid-halley-coq/coq/Clothoid_L.v; only the statement crosses the licence
# boundary and is BSD-3-Clause from birth.  Listed here too so the per-theorem
# Print Assumptions audit (scripts/audit_axioms.sh) checks it against the
# three-axiom allowlist.  No Admitted, no Axiom, no Parameter.
theories/ClothoidResidual.v
# Buffer/noder pipeline, Stage 2a seam (docs/buffer-noder-pipeline.md S2):
# offset-segment soundness -- the offset of an edge is parallel to it
# (offset_seg_dir / offset_seg_parallel) and sits at perpendicular distance
# |d| from the source line (offset_point_dist / offset_perp_dist_to_line).
# Pure Stdlib; three-axiom footprint.  No Admitted.
theories/BufferOffset.v
# Buffer/noder pipeline, Stage 2b seam (docs/buffer-noder-pipeline.md S3):
# miter-join apex geometry (JTS#180).  miter_apex is the Cramer's-rule
# intersection of the two offset lines; miter_apex_perp_dist_u/_w /
# miter_apex_on_both_offsets prove it sits at perpendicular distance d from
# both edge lines.  Pure Stdlib; three-axiom footprint.  No Admitted.
theories/BufferMiter.v
# Buffer/noder pipeline, Stage 2b seam (docs/buffer-noder-pipeline.md S3):
# miter-cap <-> half-angle soundness.  miter_numerator_sin_half ties the
# offset numerator to Azimuth.sin_half_turn(u, vneg w); miter_cap_iff_sin_half
# proves the algebraic cap (BufferMiter) and the half-angle cap
# (Azimuth.miter_ratio_le_iff) decide the same thing.  Three-axiom (Azimuth's
# sin_half_turn is sqrt-only).  No Admitted.
theories/BufferMiterAngle.v
# Buffer/noder pipeline, Stage 2b seam (docs/buffer-noder-pipeline.md S3):
