# Issue #64 / Option-A arc primitives, foundation 1: two-argument atan2 built
# on Stdlib Ratan (JTS Math.atan2 convention, range (-PI, PI]).  Headlines
# cos_atan2 / sin_atan2 characterise it as the polar angle of (x, y).  Pure
# Stdlib (no new deps) but pulls Classical_Prop.classic via Stdlib `atan`
# (cos/sin/sqrt stay clean) -- see docs/audit-exceptions.txt.  No Admitted.
theories/Atan2.v
# Issue #64 / Option-A foundation 2: signed angle between two planar vectors,
# angle_between u v = atan2 (cross u v) (dot u v) -- the robust atan2-based
# central-angle/sweep primitive (sign = orientation).  Headlines
# cos_angle_between / sin_angle_between = dot|cross / (|u||v|) via the Lagrange
# identity; plus atan2_range (-PI, PI].  Pulls classic via atan (see
# audit-exceptions).  No Admitted.
theories/AngleBetween.v
# Buffer/noder pipeline, Stage 2b seam (docs/buffer-noder-pipeline.md S3):
# round-join corner-arc relation (Roadmap target 6).  The sweep between the
# two offset normals equals the turn between the edges
# (corner_arc_sweep_eq_turn), since vperp preserves cross+dot; plus
# atan2 positive-scaling invariance to read it off the unit normals
# (corner_arc_sweep_eq_turn_unit).  Pulls classic via atan2 (see
# audit-exceptions).  No Admitted.
theories/BufferJoin.v
# Issue #64 / Option-A foundation 3 (ask #1): exact arc length s = r*theta with
