# extract_rings_valid R5 / general assembler, slice 1: the half-edge (dart)
# foundation (docs/extract-rings-proof-structure.md §5 step 1 +
# docs/dart-halfedge-foundation.md).  The combinatorial core (RingExtract)
# sidestepped the half-edge layer by taking a face walk as a pre-ordered
# closed_chain; the still-open general-overlay piece is ordering an UNORDERED
# edge set into chains.  This lays the dart layer it runs on: twin (involutive,
# injective, fixed-point-free on proper edges), darts_of (both orientations,
# closed under twin), the outgoing fan + vertex degree.  Pure dart algebra; the
# angular `next`/`face_of` orbit + its finiteness are deferred later slices.
# Axioms: the allowlisted classical-reals pair via point_eq_dec.  No Admitted.
theories/Dart.v

# extract_rings_valid R5 / general assembler, slice 3d: the signed-area
# ORIENTATION primitive for hole nesting (docs/ring-orientation.md).  Pure
# shoelace algebra: signed_area2 segs; signed_area2_app / _rev (order-invariant)
# / _map_swap (negated by endpoint swap) / _reverse_traversal (walking a chain
# backwards negates the signed area -- the orientation flip); and seg_twin_swap
# (a dart's twin swaps its segment), linking to the DCEL twin so the face across
# an edge is the orientation-reversed traversal -- the seed of outer vs hole.
# deferred (§4).  No Admitted; standard three-axiom classical-reals base.
theories/RingOrientation.v

# extract_rings_valid R5 / general assembler, slice 2e: the FINITENESS / return
# crux for face orbits (docs/orbit-cycle.md).  Pure-combinatorial heart of
# face_orbit_finite, free of geometry: an injective self-map of a finite set,
# iterated, cycles back.  For f : A -> A mapping a finite list S into itself and
# injective on S (decidable eq): iter_in (orbit stays in S, hence finite),
# iter_inj_on, iter_pigeon, and orbit_returns (some n>=1 with iter n d = d).
# Slice 2d supplies these hypotheses for next; instantiating f with the dart
# face step next o twin is slice 2f.  No Admitted; AXIOM-FREE.
theories/OrbitCycle.v

# extract_rings_valid R5 / general assembler, slice 2f: the face step next o twin
# and FACE ORBIT FINITENESS (docs/dart-face.md) -- the §9 crux, discharged.
# fstep D d = next (outgoing (dtip d) D) (twin d); under arrangement_ok (D
# twin-closed + every vertex fan fan_ok): fstep_in (orbit closure), fstep_inj
# (injective -- equal images share a vertex, reducing to slice-2d next_injective
# + twin_inj), and face_orbit_finite = orbit_returns (slice 2e) instantiated at
# f := fstep D, so iterating fstep from any dart returns to it.  Reading the
# closed orbit off as a closed_chain / ring is the deferred assembly.  No
# Admitted; axioms = the allowlisted classical-reals pair.
theories/DartFace.v

# extract_rings_valid R5 / general assembler, slice 3a: reading a face orbit off
# as a CLOSED CHAIN and thence a valid-shape ring (docs/face-chain.md).  The
# missing link between slice-2f face_orbit_finite and RingExtract.face_walk_core:
# dart_walk / face_chain (the face darts' segments); face_chain_ok (consecutive
# segments connect via next_base); face_chain_closed_chain (the orbit return
# loops the chain shut -> BufferAssembly.closed_chain); face_closed_chain_exists
# (every dart spawns a closed chain, via face_orbit_finite); and
# face_ring_valid_shape (a >=3-dart face yields a ring_closed +
# ring_has_minimum_points ring whose edges are exactly the face segments).  The
# combinatorial core of valid_polygon's outer ring for a GENERAL arrangement.
# No Admitted; axioms = the allowlisted classical-reals pair.
theories/FaceChain.v

# extract_rings_valid R5 / general assembler, slice 3b: a noded arrangement's
# face ring is ring_simple (docs/face-ring-simple.md), completing THREE of the
# four valid_polygon conditions.  seg_of d = (dbase d, dtip d) = d (Dart = Edge),
# so face segments ARE arrangement darts; face_chain_subset shows every face edge
# is in D, and ring_simple_of_subset gives ring_simple when D is
# pairwise_no_proper_cross (noded).  face_ring_combinatorial_valid bundles
# ring_closed + ring_has_minimum_points + ring_simple for a >=3-dart face.  No
# Admitted; standard three-axiom classical-reals base.
theories/FaceRingSimple.v

# extract_rings_valid R5 / general assembler, slice 3f: assembling a
# valid_polygon WITH holes, modulo the single analytic seam
